issue_obverse_figure_description_tesim: crown with two mural elements, crescent above forehead; wing above crown cap to the left and right, above this crescent and star; double pearl diadem, diadem ribbons commencing to the left and right behind the shoulders, pointing upwards; earring consisting of three elements; neck-line of tunica edged with a row of pearls; crescent on left shoulder, both shoulders decorated with crescent and stars; double row of pearls running from the shoulders to the breast, two dots on the breast; star in upper left and right field; crescent and star at 3 h, 6 h and 9 h; double dotted border
issue_obverse_legend_tesim: 2 h l. i. hslwb, 11 h l. o. GDH/ʼpzwt´ | Husraw xwarrah abzūd| “Khusro, he increased the glory”
issue_reverse_figure_description_tesim: base consisting of three elements, altar shaft, to the left and the right of the shaft ribbons pointing upwards; four altar slabs; altar flames rendered as four tiers of four, three, two and one strokes respectively; star to left of altar flames, crescent to the right; to the left and the right of the altar attendantattendants wear stylized diadem surmounted by a crescent (regnal years 11–39)

issue_reverse_legend_tesim: FELICITATI AVG S C|COS III P P
